">restraint<\/span> is also something that exists: it can exist outside yourself, as the result of somebody else\u2019s decision; but it can also exist inside you, as a fear of what other people may think or as your own feeling about what is acceptable: <span class=\"ei\">moral\/social\/cultural restraints.<\/span> A <span class=\"eb\">limitation<\/span> is more general and can be a rule that somebody makes or a fact or condition that exists.<\/span><\/div><span class=\"patterns\">Patterns<\/span><ul class=\"bullet\"><li class=\"li\">limits\/restrictions\/controls\/constraints\/restraints\/limitations <span class=\"eb\">on<\/span> something<\/li><li class=\"li\">limits\/limitations <span class=\"eb\">to<\/span> something<\/li><li class=\"li\"><span class=\"eb\">severe<\/span> limits\/restrictions\/controls\/constraints\/restraints\/limitations<\/li><li class=\"li\"><span class=\"eb\">tight<\/span> limits\/restrictions\/controls\/constraints<\/li><li class=\"li\">to <span class=\"eb\">impose\/remove<\/span> limits\/restrictions\/controls\/constraints\/restraints\/limitations <\/li><li class=\"li\">to <span class=\"eb\">lift<\/span> restrictions\/controls\/constraints\/restraints<\/li><\/ul><\/span><\/div> <\/li><li class=\"sense\"> <span class=\"def\">a point at which something stops being possible or existing<\/span><ul class=\"examples\"><li class=\"\"><span class=\"x\">She knew the limits of her power.<\/span><\/li><li class=\"\"><span class=\"x\">to <b>set\/define the limits<\/b> of something<\/span><\/li><li class=\"\"><span class=\"x\">to <b>push\/test the limits<\/b> of something<\/span><\/li><li class=\"\"><span class=\"x\">It's a movie that stretches the limits of believability.<\/span><\/li><li class=\"\"><span class=\"x\">His arrogance <b>knew<\/b> <span class=\"gloss\">(= had)<\/span> <b>no limits<\/b>.<\/span><\/li><li class=\"\"> <b>limit to something<\/b> <span class=\"x\">There is a limit to the amount of pain we can bear.<\/span><\/li><li class=\"\">